I play the Palms course almost weekly and have played the Lakes course several times.  Even through the brutally hot Phoenix summer the courses are in very good shape.  If you're a beginner (or a seasoned player looking to tune-up your irons) the Lakes course has a fun layout with mostly par 3s and short par 4s.  The Palms course presents challenges for golfers at any level.

